# Barry O's Old Market Tavern — Cursor Rules
# Royal Oak, MI · Est. 1985 · barryostavern.com
# Stack: MongoDB · Express · React · Node.js (TypeScript)
# Services: Vercel (client) · Railway (server) · MongoDB Atlas · Auth0 · Cloudinary

## WHAT THIS PROJECT IS

A neighborhood Irish tavern migrating off WordPress. Two experiences:
1. A public marketing site (read-mostly, SSR-friendly React)
2. A staff dashboard (auth-gated SPA, all content management)

The owner is non-technical. Dashboard language must be plain English.
Events are sporadic — an empty calendar is a NORMAL state, not an error.

## CRITICAL NON-NEGOTIABLES (read before every session)

- No stranger-submitted photo ever reaches the public site without an explicit human approval click.
- Consent checkbox is enforced SERVER-SIDE on POST /api/submissions — never trust the UI alone.
- EXIF data is stripped from every uploaded image during the pipeline (sharp library).
- Uploaded images are stored in a private Cloudinary folder until approved; approval moves them to public.
- All /api/admin/* routes require Auth0 JWT — no exceptions.
- Rate limiting is active on POST /api/submissions.

