## DESIGN SYSTEM (from approved mockups)

These CSS custom properties are the single source of truth. Use them; don't invent new colors.

```css
--bg: #070a07
--side: #0a0e0a
--panel: #0f140f
--panel-2: #131913
--green: #1f9c4d
--green-bright: #27b85c
--green-deep: #0f5c2e
--gold: #c9a44c
--amber: #e0a93c
--red: #e25555
--text: #f1f4f0
--muted: #8b988d
--line: rgba(255,255,255,.08)
--green-line: rgba(39,184,92,.3)
```

Fonts: Anton (display/headers), Barlow (body), Kaushan Script (brand script), Oswald (labels/nav/UI)
Border-radius: 8px cards, 12px panels, 20px pills
The design is dark, Irish pub, not generic SaaS dark mode. Every component must feel like it belongs.

## DATA MODELS (Mongoose)

### Event
```typescript
{ type: 'sports'|'holiday'|'shuttle'|'community', title, description, date: Date,
  timeLabel: string, createdBy: ObjectId }
// "Upcoming" = query filter (date >= now). Never stored as a status field.
```

### Submission (UGC photos)
```typescript
{ submitterName, submitterEmail?, caption, imageUrl, thumbnailUrl,
  status: 'pending'|'approved'|'rejected',  // default 'pending'
  consent: true,          // REQUIRED — reject if false server-side
  consentText: string,    // snapshot of the exact wording they agreed to
  exifStripped: true, cloudinaryPublicId, cloudinaryFolder,
  review: { reviewedBy, reviewedAt }, submitterIpHash }
```

### SiteSettings (singleton — find-or-create on boot)
```typescript
{ announcement: { enabled, message, linkTarget },
  christmasParty: { enabled, title, date, note, ticketUrl },
  hero: { videoUrl, posterUrl },
  hours: [{ label, value, order }],
  contact: { address, phone }, about,
  instagram: { handle, showApprovedInGallery } }
```

### User (staff)
```typescript
{ name, email, passwordHash, role: 'manager'|'staff' }
// Auth0 manages authentication; User stores role + profile metadata.
```

## API ROUTES

### Public (no auth)
- GET  /api/site          → SiteSettings (public fields only)
- GET  /api/events        → upcoming events only (date >= now), asc
- GET  /api/gallery       → approved submissions
- POST /api/submissions   → create pending submission (multipart, rate-limited)

### Admin (Auth0 JWT required on all)
- POST   /api/auth/login
- GET    /api/admin/submissions?status=pending|approved|rejected
- PATCH  /api/admin/submissions/:id   → { status }
- DELETE /api/admin/submissions/:id
- GET    /api/admin/events            → all events incl. past
- POST   /api/admin/events
- PATCH  /api/admin/events/:id
- DELETE /api/admin/events/:id
- GET    /api/admin/site
- PUT    /api/admin/site
- POST   /api/admin/media/hero

## IMAGE UPLOAD PIPELINE (server-side, every submission)
1. Validate MIME type (image/jpeg, image/png, image/webp only)
2. Enforce MAX_UPLOAD_BYTES (default 8MB)
3. Re-encode with sharp → strips EXIF, normalizes format
4. Generate thumbnail (400px wide)
5. Upload original + thumb to Cloudinary private folder (pending/)
6. Store Cloudinary public_id + secure_url in Submission
7. On approve: move asset from pending/ → public/ folder via Cloudinary API
8. On reject/delete: destroy Cloudinary asset

## CODING CONVENTIONS

### TypeScript
- Strict mode always
- Interfaces for all data shapes; export from a types/ index
- Explicit return types on service functions and route handlers

### React
- Functional components + hooks only
- Custom hook for each major data fetch (useEvents, useSubmissions, useSiteSettings)
- Zero raw fetch() calls in components — everything through services/
- Tailwind for layout/spacing, CSS variables for brand colors
- Component folders: ComponentName/index.tsx + ComponentName.module.css if needed

### Express
- asyncHandler wrapper on every route — no unhandled promise rejections
- All admin routes grouped under checkJwt middleware at the router level
- Consistent JSON response shape: { data, error?, meta? }
- Never return a Mongoose document directly — call .toObject() or shape it

### Error handling
- 400 Bad Request: validation failures (missing consent, bad MIME, etc.)
- 401 Unauthorized: missing/invalid token
- 403 Forbidden: valid token, wrong role
- 404 Not Found: resource not found
- 429 Too Many Requests: rate limit hit (submissions endpoint)
- 500: unexpected — log fully, return generic message

## ENVIRONMENT VARIABLES

### server/.env
```
PORT=3001
NODE_ENV=development
MONGODB_URI=
AUTH0_DOMAIN=
AUTH0_AUDIENCE=
CLOUDINARY_URL=
CLOUDINARY_PENDING_FOLDER=barryos/pending
CLOUDINARY_PUBLIC_FOLDER=barryos/gallery
MAX_UPLOAD_BYTES=8000000
RATE_LIMIT_WINDOW_MS=900000
RATE_LIMIT_MAX_SUBMISSIONS=10
```

### client/.env
```
VITE_API_URL=http://localhost:3001/api
VITE_AUTH0_DOMAIN=
VITE_AUTH0_CLIENT_ID=
VITE_AUTH0_AUDIENCE=
```

## THINGS TO NEVER DO

- Never auto-publish a submission. status defaults to 'pending'. Always.
- Never return EXIF data to the client. Strip it before storage.
- Never show "No events scheduled" to the public. Use EvergreenPanel instead.
- Never accept a submission where consent !== true — validate server-side.
- Never commit secrets. All env vars in .env files, never in source.
- Never store the hero video in MongoDB. Store the URL; video lives in Cloudinary/S3.
- Never use React state or localStorage for auth state — use Auth0 hooks.

## FEATURE FLAGS / CONTENT TOGGLES

Both announcement bar and Christmas CTA are controlled by boolean `enabled` fields in SiteSettings.
When disabled: the component renders null — no empty shell, no placeholder.
The public EventsGrid checks for upcoming events; if none, renders EvergreenPanel. Never an error state.

## TESTING THE DUAL STATE

The EvergreenPanel → EventsGrid toggle is critical. Before any PR touching EventsGrid:
- Test with 0 upcoming events → must show EvergreenPanel
- Test with 1+ upcoming events → must show event cards
- Test with only past-dated events → must show EvergreenPanel (past events excluded)

## COMMIT CONVENTIONS

See docs/GIT_CONVENTIONS.md for full rules. Short form:
feat(scope): description     — new feature
fix(scope): description      — bug fix
chore(scope): description    — config, deps, tooling
docs(scope): description     — documentation only
refactor(scope): description — no behavior change
test(scope): description     — tests only

Scopes: client, server, api, models, auth, submissions, events, settings, gallery, admin, deploy

